COMPONENT NAME: IKM Oracle Control Append COMPONENT VERSION: 12.1.3.1 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 12.1.3.0.0 and above
DESCRIPTION: - Integrates data into an Oracle target table in control append mode. - all rows are inserted. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions.
REQUIREMENTS: - The Update Key defined in the interface is mandatory.
RESTRICTIONS: - When working with journalized data, if the "Synchronize deletions from journal" is executed, the deleted rows on the target are committed - The TRUNCATE option cannot work if the target table is referenced by another table (foreign key) - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore. - The option FLOW_TABLE_OPTION is set by default to NOLOGGING. Set it to whitespace if the interface runs on an Oracle 7 database - Deletes are commited regardless of the COMMIT option - The ANALYZE_TARGET option will evaluate correct statistics only if COMMIT is set to Yes. Otherwise, the IKM will gather statistics based on old data.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface
Commit all data inserted or updated in the target datastore.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface.
Check this option if you wish to perform flow control.
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you wish to truncate the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you wish to create the target table.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

Use this option to specify the attributes for the integration table at create time and used for increasing performance. This option is set by default to NOLOGGING (valid only from Oracle v8). This option may be left empty.
This option enables/disables index creation on flow table.
This option affects the use of PURGE key word and the way statistics are collected: Values PURGE STATS 10 Yes DBMS_STATS 9 No DBMS_STATS 8 No ANALYZE

This option generates an extra validation step during development. Validations performed are:
- validation of KM option COMPATIBLE - validation of RDBMS version of staging database - validation of KM option DETECTION_STRATEGY
This option should be turned off for all production use in particular for high-frequency execution. There is not added value in production, only processing overhead.
Note : Execute this this grant as sys to modify the permissions of the target data server schema
grant select on v_$parameter to <user>;
Check this option if you wish to analyze the target table before loading data into the integration table.
Hint for loading integration table. The hint value needs to be enclosed into /*+ */.
Use this option to specify the hint to be used while loading the integration table. Enclose the hint value into /*+ */.
Insert hint to be used while loading data into integration table
Insert hint to be used while loading data into target table.
Disable/enable constraints before/after the data is loaded into target table
None, Disable, Enable, Disable and Enable
Select the appropriate value to disable/enable constraints before/after the data is loaded into target table
Disable/enable indexes before/after the data is loaded into target table
None, Disable, Enable, Enable Rebuild Online, Disable and Enable, Disable and Enable Rebuild Online
Select the appropriate value to disable/enable indexes before/after the data is loaded into target table

<% String indexes = odiRef.getOption("INDEXES");
if (indexes.equals("Disable") || indexes.equals("Disable and Enable") || indexes.equals("Disable and Enable Rebuild Online")) { 
%>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selIdxQuery = "select index_name from all_indexes where table_owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status='VALID'"

try {
  selIdxStmt = connection.createStatement();
  selIdxResultSet = selIdxStmt.executeQuery(selIdxQuery);
  alterStmt = connection.createStatement()

  while (selIdxResultSet.next()) {
     alterSql = "alter index <%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>."+selIdxResultSet.getString("index_name")+" unusable"
     odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
     alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
  }
  alterSql = "alter session set SKIP_UNUSABLE_INDEXES = true";
  odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
  alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxResultSet != null) { try { selIdxResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxStmt != null) { try { selIdxStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}

<%}%>

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("FLOW_CONTROL").equals("1")) { %>
delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=odiRef.getColList("", odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME] = I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand \t", "", "UK")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' ) <%}%>

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("FLOW_CONTROL").equals("1") ) { %> insert /*+ <%=odiRef.getOption("HINT_INSERT_TARGET")%> */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <% } else { %> insert /*+ <%=odiRef.getOption("HINT_INSERT_TARGET")%> */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> )
select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(",", "[EXPRESSION]", ",
	", "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> FROM ( <%for (int i=odiRef.getDataSetMin(); i <= odiRef.getDataSetMax(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION] [COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <%} else {%> (1=1) <% } %> <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%> ) <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> ODI_GET_FROM
<% } %>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if (new Integer(odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )).intValue() < 9 ) { %>
analyze table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> estimate statistics
<% } else { %>
begin dbms_stats.gather_table_stats( ownname => '<%=odiRef.getInfo( "DEST_SCHEMA" )%>', tabname => '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%>', estimate_percent => 10 ); end;
<% }; %>

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS").equals("1")) { %> drop table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "W")%> <% if (new Integer(odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )).intValue() >= 10 ) { out.print( "purge" ); }; %> <% } else { %> /* DELETE_TEMPORARY_OBJECTS = false, temporary objects are not deleted */ <% } %>

<% if (new Integer(odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )).intValue() < 9 ) { %>
analyze table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> estimate statistics
<% } else { %>
begin dbms_stats.gather_table_stats( ownname => '<%=odiRef.getInfo( "DEST_SCHEMA" )%>', tabname => '<%=odiRef.getTargetTable("RES_NAME")%>', estimate_percent => 10 ); end;
<% }; %>

<% if ("C".equals(odiRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=odiRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

<% if (new Integer(odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )).intValue() < 9 ) { %>
analyze table <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> estimate statistics
<% } else { %>
begin dbms_stats.gather_table_stats( ownname => '<%=odiRef.getInfo( "DEST_WORK_SCHEMA" )%>', tabname => '<%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A").replaceAll("","").replaceAll("..>",".replaceAll(odiRef.getInfo( \\u0022DEST_WORK_SCHEMA\\u0022 )+\\u0022.\\u0022,\\u0022\\u0022)?>")%>', estimate_percent => 10 ); end;
<% }; %>

insert /*+ <%=odiRef.getOption("HINT_INSERT_FLOW")%> */ into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", "","((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> ) <%for (int i=odiRef.getDataSetMin(); i <= odiRef.getDataSetMax(); i++){%> <%=odiRef.getDataSet(i, "Operator")%> select <%=odiRef.getOption("HINT_SELECT")%> <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList(i,"", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom(i)%> where <% if (odiRef.getDataSet(i, "HAS_JRN").equals("1")) { %> JRN_FLAG <> 'D' <%} else {%> (1=1) <% } %> <%=odiRef.getJoin(i)%> <%=odiRef.getFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter(i)%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy(i)%> <%=odiRef.getHaving(i)%> <%}%>

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("RECYCLE_ERRORS").equals("1")) { %> insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> ( <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG) AND REW)")%>, IND_UPDATE ) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS OR UPD) AND NOT TRG) AND REW)")%>, 'I' IND_UPDATE from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME] = E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ODI_ORIGIN = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ODI_ERR_TYPE = '<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>' <% } else { %> /* RECYCLE_ERRORS = false, errors will not be recycled */ <% } %>

if #V0 < <%=odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )%>: raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-ORA-10000", "ODIKM-ORA-10000: You are using RDBMS version {0}.{1}. This version does not support IKM COMPATIBLE={2}.", ["#V0","#V1",<%=odiRef.getOption( "COMPATIBLE" )%>])

/* This query returns the COMPATIBLE setting of the RDBMS */ select case when upper(name) = 'COMPATIBLE' then to_number(substr(value, 1, instr(value, '.',1,1)-1)) else null end v0, case when upper(name) = 'COMPATIBLE' then to_number(substr(value, instr(value, '.',1,1)+1, instr(value, '.',1,2)-instr(value, '.',1,1)-1)) else null end v1 from v$parameter where upper(name) = 'COMPATIBLE'

<%if ( odiRef.getOption("CREATE_FLOW_INDEX").equals("1")) { %> create index <%=odiRef.getObjectName("L", odiRef.getTableName("INT_SHORT_NAME")+"_UK", "W")%> on <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "UK")%>) <%=odiRef.getOption("FLOW_TABLE_OPTIONS")%> <% } else { %> /* Index creation is disabled by CREATE_FLOW_INDEX option */ <% } %>

<% if (odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Enable") || odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable and Enable")) { %>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selConsQuery = "select constraint_name from all_constraints where owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status = 'DISABLED'"
try {
  selConsStmt = connection.createStatement()
  selConsResultSet = selConsStmt.executeQuery(selConsQuery) 

  alterStmt = connection.createStatement();
  
  exception = null
  strBuilder = null
  while (selConsResultSet.next()) {
    try {
      alterSql = "alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> enable constraint "+selConsResultSet.getString("constraint_name")
      odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
      alterStmt.execute(alterSql)
    } catch (java.sql.SQLException e) {
      if (exception == null) {
        strBuilder = new StringBuilder(System.getProperty("line.separator"))
        exception = e
      }
      strBuilder.append(e.getMessage())
      odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.SEVERE, "Executing the statement '"+alterSql+"' failed."+e.getMessage())
    }
  }
  
  if (exception != null) {
    odiEx = new OdiKMException("ODIKM-ORA-10005", "ODIKM-ORA-10005: Enabling constraints failed. {0} ", strBuilder.toString())
    odiEx.addSuppressed(exception)
    throw odiEx
  }   
  
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsResultSet != null) { try { selConsResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsStmt != null) { try { selConsStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
}

<%}%>

<% String indexes = odiRef.getOption("INDEXES");
if (indexes.equals("Enable") || 
    indexes.equals("Enable Rebuild Online") || 
    indexes.equals("Disable and Enable") || 
    indexes.equals("Disable and Enable Rebuild Online")) { 
%>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selIdxQuery = "select index_name from all_indexes where table_owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status = 'UNUSABLE'"

try {
  selIdxStmt = connection.createStatement();
  selIdxResultSet = selIdxStmt.executeQuery(selIdxQuery);
  alterStmt = connection.createStatement()

  while (selIdxResultSet.next()) {
     alterSql = "alter index <%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>."+selIdxResultSet.getString("index_name")+" rebuild"
     <% if (indexes.equals("Enable Rebuild Online") || 
            indexes.equals("Disable and Enable Rebuild Online")) { 
     %>
     alterSql += " online"
     <%}%>
     odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
     alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
  }
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxResultSet != null) { try { selIdxResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selIdxStmt != null) { try { selIdxStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}

<%}%>

<% if (odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable") || odiRef.getOption("CONSTRAINTS").equals("Disable and Enable")) { %>

connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection( "DEST" )
selConsQuery = "select constraint_name from all_constraints where owner = '<%= odiRef.getSchemaName() %>' and table_name = '<%= odiRef.getTargetTable("TABLE_NAME") %>' and status = 'ENABLED'"

try {
  selConsStmt = connection.createStatement();
  selConsResultSet = selConsStmt.executeQuery(selConsQuery);
  alterStmt = connection.createStatement()

  while (selConsResultSet.next()) {
     alterSql = "alter table <%=odiRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> disable constraint "+selConsResultSet.getString("constraint_name")
     odiRef.getLogger().log(java.util.logging.Level.INFO, "Executing the statement : " + alterSql)
     alterStmt.execute(alterSql);
  }
} finally {
  if (alterStmt != null) { try { alterStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsResultSet != null) { try { selConsResultSet.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }
  if (selConsStmt != null) { try { selConsStmt.close() } catch (e) {e.printStackTrace()} }  
}

<%}%>
